  "description": "Conditional probability is the probability of one event given that another event has already occurred or is known to be true. It answers questions like: what is the probability it will rain tomorrow, given that the barometric pressure is falling? What is the probability a patient has a disease, given that their test came back positive? The \u0026ldquo;given\u0026rdquo; clause changes the calculation by restricting attention to a subset of the possible outcomes.\n",
